data.title: Writing Adolescent Fiction/Character names/French
data.text:
In French, diminutives like Mimi, Dédé and Pierrot are only used by children and also seen as outdated.

These names are good for French and French-Canadians. If you have a teenage character from France today, be very careful to not fall into clichés. Like naming a young character Charles, Jean, and François or Ghislaine, Monique, and Louise.
